5 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1005, is
6 amended to read as follows:
7 Section 1005. (a) A. Examinations shall be uniform and shall
8 be practical in nature but sufficiently strict to test the
9 qualification and fitness of the applicant as a journeyman plumber
10 or as a plumbing contractor, as the case may be. It An examination
11 shall be in whole or in part in writing.
12 (b) B. Regular examinations shall be held at least twice each
13 year and special examinations may be fixed by the Oklahoma State
14 Committee of Plumbing Examiners. Any applicant initially failing to
15 pass the examination shall not be permitted to take another
16 examination for a period of thirty (30) days, and thereafter any
17 such applicant subsequently failing to pass the examination shall
18 not be permitted to take a subsequent examination for a period of
19 ninety (90) days.
20 C. An applicant for a residential journeyman plumber
21 examination shall be eighteen (18) years of age or older and have:
22 1. Three (3) years of experience in the plumbing trade while
23 employed by a licensed plumbing contractor;
24
